



# APPLICATION 07: SPACE

## Sovereign, Radiation-Hardened, Ultra-Low-Energy AI for Spacecraft and Satellite Systems

---

### The Problem

| **Current Space AI** | **Reality** |
|---|---|
| **Cloud-dependent** | No cloud in space — latency, bandwidth, and connectivity are impossible |
| **High energy** | 500,000 µJ per query — drains spacecraft power budgets |
| **Radiation sensitivity** | Stochastic AI on GPUs — no radiation hardening |
| **Stochastic outputs** | Cannot be trusted in mission-critical space operations |
| **Latency** | 50 ms cloud round-trip — impossible in deep space |
| **Memory footprint** | 14,000 MB — impossible on spacecraft with limited memory |

**Current AI cannot be deployed in space. The gap is absolute.**

---

### The Space Environment

| **Challenge** | **Reality** |
|---|---|
| **Radiation** | Single-event upsets (SEUs), total ionizing dose (TID) — kills electronics |
| **Power** | Solar panels provide limited power — every µJ counts |
| **Memory** | Spacecraft have limited SRAM/DRAM — 0.7 MB is a gift |
| **Latency** | Deep space communication delays — hours, not milliseconds |
| **Autonomy** | No ground control — AI must be deterministic and self-sufficient |
| **Cooling** | No water or air cooling in vacuum — passive only |

**ST-T1024 is designed for the space environment. The architecture is radiation-tolerant by construction.**

---

